üìå Definition
==================
Combining or merging two or more types of data is known as Concatenation.

In Java, concatenation is achieved using the + (plus) operator.

ASCII Values
--------------
Characters	ASCII Range
A to Z	- 65 to 90
a to z	- 97 to 122
0 to 9	- 48 to 57
Operations Using + Operator in Java
1Ô∏è‚É£ Number
------------
Operation	Result
Number + Number	- Addition
Number + Character	- Addition (Character converted to ASCII)
Number + String	- Concatenation
Number + Boolean	- ‚ùå Compile Time Error (CTE)
Example:
----------
System.out.println(10 + 20);      // 30
System.out.println(10 + 'A');     // 75 (10 + 65)
System.out.println(10 + "20");    // 1020
// System.out.println(10 + true); // CTE
2Ô∏è‚É£ Character
--------------
Operation	Result
Character + Number	- Addition
Character + Character	- Addition (ASCII values added)
Character + String	- Concatenation
Character + Boolean	- ‚ùå Compile Time Error (CTE)
Example:
----------
System.out.println('A' + 10);      // 75
System.out.println('A' + 'B');     // 131 (65 + 66)
System.out.println('A' + "B");     // AB
// System.out.println('A' + true); // CTE
3Ô∏è‚É£ String
------------
If any one operand is a String, the result is always Concatenation.

Operation	Result
String + Number	- Concatenation
String + Character	- Concatenation
String + String	- Concatenation
String + Boolean	- Concatenation
Example:
----------
System.out.println("Hello" + 10);      // Hello10
System.out.println("Hello" + 'A');     // HelloA
System.out.println("Hello" + "Java");  // HelloJava
System.out.println("Hello" + true);    // Hellotrue
4Ô∏è‚É£ Boolean
------------
Operation	Result
Boolean + Number	- ‚ùå Compile Time Error (CTE)
Boolean + Character	- ‚ùå Compile Time Error (CTE)
Boolean + String	- Concatenation
Boolean + Boolean	- ‚ùå Compile Time Error (CTE)
Example:
---------
// System.out.println(true + 10);    // CTE
// System.out.println(true + 'A');   // CTE
System.out.println(true + "Java");   // trueJava
// System.out.println(true + false); // CTE
‚úÖ Important Rule to Remember
------------------------------
üîπ If at least one operand is a String, the result is always Concatenation.
üîπ If both operands are numeric (or characters), Java performs Addition.
üîπ Boolean cannot be added using + except with String.
